The paper deals with the computational power of Population Protocols (PP) under unreliable and weaker interaction models. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the simulation of PP under different interaction models, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Simulation and Modeling (cs.SC). The use of omission failures and one-way communications in PP also relates to the study of Fault Tolerance (cs.DS) and Self-Organizing Systems (cs.SI).
